{"title_page": "Natalie Hall", "text_new": "{{short description|Canadian actress}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Natalie Hall\n| image = Natalie Hall (cropped).jpg\n| image_size =\n| caption = Natalie Hall speaking at the 2014 [[WonderCon]]\n| birth_name = Natalie Elise Hall\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=y|1990|01|25}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://natalie-hall.net/photos/displayimage.php?pid=10081&fullsize=1 |title=ABC Soaps In Depth > Featured Interviews |access-date=August 17, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723215637/http://natalie-hall.net/photos/displayimage.php?pid=10081&fullsize=1 |archive-date=July 23, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]], Canada<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hallmarkchannel.com/microsites/cast.aspx?simscode=419-32150&pageid=3220&castid=2662 |title=Natalie Hall - Love's Christmas Journey - Cast |publisher=Hallmark Channel |date= |accessdate=August 21, 2013}}</ref>\n| occupation = Actress\n| years_active = 2004\u2013Present\n| notable_works = ''[[All My Children]]''\n}}\n'''Natalie Elise Hall'''<ref name=BiographySopa>{{cite web|title=Natalie Hall Biography - Sopa Opera Digest|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/natalie-hall-bio|publisher=Soap Opera Digest|accessdate=April 6, 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407084741/http://www.soapoperadigest.com/natalie-hall-bio|archivedate=April 7, 2014|df=}}</ref> (born January 25, 1990)<ref name=BiographySopa /> is a Canadian actress and singer. She has appeared in various Broadway, film and TV productions. Her first TV appearance was when she portrayed the role of [[Colby Chandler (All My Children)|Colby Chandler]] on the soap opera ''[[All My Children]]'' from 2009 to 2011. Hall appeared opposite [[Miles Teller]], [[Josh Brolin]] and [[Jeff Bridges]] in the 2017 film ''[[Only the Brave (2017 film)|Only the Brave]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nNatalie grew up in Vancouver, British Columbia prior to moving to New York to pursue roles on Broadway. Hall's mother was a ballerina. Hall grew up with two brothers, of which she has said \"I grew up loving the arts but I also was such a tomboy, I loved sports and was very competitive.\" She grew up playing soccer on an all-boys soccer team.<ref name=BiographySopa />\n\nShe performed as Val in the Broadway  production of ''[[A Chorus Line]]''.<ref name=BiographySopa /> Hall spoke about her first role, saying \"It was an amazing experience. I had to grow up so fast working with such talent on a big stage\". Her portrayal of Val earned her a [[Ovation (award)|Ovation award]]. Hall moved to [[New York City]] to pursue her dreams of [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] and TV stardom, and relocated to Los Angeles in 2010.<ref name=BiographySopa />\n\n==Career==\n===Acting===\n[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] announced that Hall had been cast in the role of [[Colby Chandler (All My Children)|Colby Chandler]] in the soap ''[[All My Children]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soaps.sheknows.com/allmychildren/news/id/5587/|title=Breaking News! All My Children Casts Natalie Hall as Colby!|date=October 3, 2009|work=Soaps She Knows|publisher=Atomic Online|accessdate=May 6, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402104619/http://soaps.sheknows.com/allmychildren/news/id/5587/|archive-date=April 2, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> Hall made her debut on November 25, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boards.soapcentral.com/amc/news/2009/1005-moncrief.php|title=Brianne Moncrief out, Colby Chandler recast|date=September 30, 2009|first=Dan J.|last=Kroll|work=[[SoapCentral]]|accessdate=May 6, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222213031/http://www.boards.soapcentral.com/amc/news/2009/1005-moncrief.php|archivedate=February 22, 2014|df=}}</ref> Hall filmed her first scenes in mid October just before the show relocated to [[Los Angeles]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://michaelfairmansoaps.com/news/natalie-hall-in-as-new-colby-on-amc/2009/10/02/|title=Natalie Hall IN as new Colby on \"AMC\"!|date=October 2, 2009|first=Michael|last=Fairman|work=On-Air On-Soaps|accessdate=May 6, 2013}}</ref> Hall made her last appearance in the final network broadcast of ''All My Children'' on September 23, 2011.\n\nOn June 29, 2011, it was announced that Hall would be replacing Natalie Floyd as Hanna's soon-to-be stepsister, Kate Randall, in the [[ABC Family]] series ''[[Pretty Little Liars]]'', playing the role until 2012.<ref>{{cite web |last=Bonner |first=Mehera |url=http://www.wetpaint.com/pretty-little-liars/articles/natalie-hall-replaces-natalie-floyd-as-hannas-wicked-stepsister-kate-on-pretty-little-liars |title=Natalie Hall Replaces Natalie Floyd as Hanna's Wicked Stepsister, Kate, on Pretty Little Liars |publisher=[[Wetpaint]] |date=June 29, 2011 |accessdate=July 7, 2011}}</ref> She played Ellie King n\u00e9e Davis, in ''[[Love's Christmas Journey]]'', a four-part mini-series in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/all-my-children-actress-star-220942 |title='All My Children' Actress to Star in Hallmark Mini 'Love's Christmas Journey' (Exclusive) |publisher=Hollywoodreporter.com |date=October 8, 2011 |accessdate=August 21, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, she was cast as Taylor in [[The CW]] series ''[[Star-Crossed (TV series)|Star-Crossed]]''.<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.caravanstyliststudio.com/natalie-hall-staring-in-star-crossed-a-new-show-on-the-cw-visits-caravan-stylist-studio-at-the-carlton-hotel/4133/ |title=Natalie Hall starring in \"Star Crossed\" a new show on the CW visits Caravan Stylist Studio at The Carlton Hotel |publisher=Caravan Stylist Studio |date=May 23, 2013 |accessdate=August 21, 2013}}</ref> Hall described her character as the \"Queen Bee with a big heart\" and a risk-taker in love.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Vogt|first1=Tiffany|title=STAR-CROSSED Scoop: Natalie Hall Talks Playing the Queen Bee of Marshall High|url=http://www.thetvaddict.com/2014/02/12/star-crossed-scoop-natalie-hall-talks-playing-the-queen-bee-of-marshall-high/|publisher=The TV Addict|accessdate=October 31, 2014}}</ref> Hall played Britney in the series revival of [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]] comedy-drama ''[[Drop Dead Diva]]'' originally for two episodes however came back for another episode.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Nededog|first1=Jethro|title=\u2018Pretty Little Liars\u2019 Natalie Hall in, Josh Stamberg out at \u2018Drop Dead Diva\u2019|url=https://www.thewrap.com/tv/article/pretty-little-liars-natalie-hall-josh-stamberg-out-drop-dead-diva-95586/|publisher=The Wrap|accessdate=October 31, 2014}}</ref> Hall joined the cast of [[HBO]]'s ''[[True Blood]]'' for its [[True Blood (season 7)|final season]], appearing as resident villain [[Sarah Newlin]]'s ([[Anna Camp]]) newly turned vampire sister, Amber Mills, for three episodes.<ref name=FaveMag>{{cite web|last1=Tsoumbakos|first1=Rachel|title=True Blood\u2019s Natalie Hall Graces Cover of Fave Magazine: The Canadian Fashion Magazine Available from October 2014|url=http://truebloodnet.com/true-bloods-natalie-hall-graces-cover-of-fave-magazine/|accessdate=October 31, 2014}}</ref> She appeared on the cover of the Canadian [[fashion magazine]] ''Fave''.<ref name=FaveMag />\n\nHall guested starred in [[USA Network]] medical [[comedy-drama]] ''[[Royal Pains]]'' as Hope, a [[burlesque]] dancer who turns to Jeremiah for help when she begins experiencing pain during her act.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deadline.com/2014/06/royal-pains-season-six-cast-usa-network/|title=5 Set For Season 6 Of USA\u2019s \u2018Royal Pains\u2019|publisher=Deadline.com|date=June 4, 2014|accessdate=June 5, 2014}}</ref> Hall is also a member of the Prestigious \"Actors Studio\" in New York. Hall was most recently cast in the upcoming untitled Marc Cherry ABC pilot. Natalie Hall was seen in UnREAL season four on Lifetime. Also, in the CW series ''[[Charmed]]'' playing Lucy.\n\n===Music===\nHall performs in various musicals in New York. Hall was trained at the London Academy of Ballet and graduated with honors of distinction in dance when she was sixteen. In the film ''[[Rising Stars (film)|Rising Stars]]'', Hall performed \"Better with You\", the music video for the song featuring Hall was later released.<ref name=RisingStars>{{cite web|title=Rising Stars (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/rising-stars-original-motion/id404326073|publisher=[[iTunes]]|accessdate=April 7, 2014}}</ref> She was also featured in the song \"Free To Fall\" which also appeared in the film and the official soundtrack.<ref name=RisingStars/> Hall performed \"[[Hallelujah I Love Her So]]\" by [[Ray Charles]] at the \"[[It Gets Better Project]]'s \"A Better Holiday\" concert benefiting The Ali Forney Center on December 16, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|last=Alexander|first=Clint|title=Natalie Hall - \"Hallelujah I Love Her So\"|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M3b0snYA3Qg|accessdate=April 7, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n<!-- Please note: \"rowspan\" breaks table sortability. -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|2004\n|''Have You Heard? Secret Central''\n|Tes Taylor\n|\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Rising Stars (film)|Rising Stars]]''\n|Brenna\n|\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[+1 (film)|+1]]''\n|Melanie\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''Lucky N#mbr''\n|Nikki Page\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''Simple Little Lives''\n|Kaylee\n|\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''{{sortname|The|Curse of Sleeping Beauty}}''\n| Linda Coleman\n| \n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Summer of 8]]''\n|Jen\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[The Boy Downstairs]]''\n|Ivy\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Only the Brave (2017 film)|''Only the Brave'']]''\n|Natalie Johnson\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n<!-- Please note: \"rowspan\" breaks table sortability. -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|2008\n|''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]''\n|Shelby Crawford\n|Episode: \"Streetwise\"\n|- \n|2009\n|''{{sortname|The|Good Wife}}''\n|Maura\n|Episode: \"Stripped\"\n|-\n|2009\u201311\n|''[[All My Children]]''\n|[[Colby Chandler (All My Children)|Colby Chandler]]\n|Role held: November 25, 2009 \u2013 September 23, 2011\n|-\n|2011\u201312\n|''[[Pretty Little Liars (TV series)|Pretty Little Liars]]''\n|Kate Randall\n|Recurring role (season 2); 5 episodes\n|- \n|2011\n|''[[Love's Christmas Journey]]''\n|Ellie Davis King\n|Television film\n|-\n|2012\n|''{{sortname|The|Seven Year Hitch|nolink=1}}''\n|Jennifer\n|Television film\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation]]''\n|Katy Hill\n|Episode: \"Last Woman Standing\"\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[Drop Dead Diva]]''\n|Britney\n|3 episodes\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[Star-Crossed (TV series)|Star-Crossed]]''\n|Taylor Beecham\n|Main role; 11 episodes\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[Royal Pains]]''\n|Hope\n|Episode: \"Everybody Loves Ray, Man\"\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[True Blood]]''\n|Amber Mills\n|3 episodes\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[Royal Pains]]''\n|Tasha\n|Episode: \"Electric Youth\"\n|- \n|2017\n|''[[Shades of Blue]]''\n|Bianci's Girlfriend \n|3 episodes\n|- \n|2017\n|''[[NCIS: New Orleans]]''\n|Chloe Myles \n|Episode: \"Acceptable Loss\"\n|- \n|2018\n|''[[Unreal (TV series)|Unreal]]''\n|Candy Coco  \n|8 episodes\n|-\n|2018\u201319\n|''[[Charmed (2018 TV series)|Charmed]]''\n|Lucy\n|Recurring role, season 1\n|-\n|2019\n|''A Winter Princess''\n|Carly / Princess Carlotta\n|Television film ([[Hallmark Channel|Hallmark]])\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''You\u2019re Bacon Me Crazy''\n| Cleo Morelli\n| Television film (Hallmark Channel) \n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|2834250}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hall, Natalie}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Vancouver]]\n[[Category:Canadian child actresses]]\n[[Category:Canadian emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Canadian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Canadian musical theatre actresses]]\n[[Category:Canadian soap opera actresses]]\n[[Category:Canadian television actresses]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Canadian actress}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Natalie Hall\n| image = Natalie Hall (cropped).jpg\n| image_size =\n| caption = Natalie Hall speaking at the 2014 [[WonderCon]]\n| birth_name = Natalie Elise Hall\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=y|1990|01|25}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://natalie-hall.net/photos/displayimage.php?pid=10081&fullsize=1 |title=ABC Soaps In Depth > Featured Interviews |access-date=August 17, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723215637/http://natalie-hall.net/photos/displayimage.php?pid=10081&fullsize=1 |archive-date=July 23, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]], Canada<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hallmarkchannel.com/microsites/cast.aspx?simscode=419-32150&pageid=3220&castid=2662 |title=Natalie Hall - Love's Christmas Journey - Cast |publisher=Hallmark Channel |date= |accessdate=August 21, 2013}}</ref>\n| occupation = Actress\n| years_active = 2004\u2013Present\n| notable_works = ''[[All My Children]]''\n}}\n'''Natalie Elise Hall'''<ref name=BiographySopa>{{cite web|title=Natalie Hall Biography - Sopa Opera Digest|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/natalie-hall-bio|publisher=Soap Opera Digest|accessdate=April 6, 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407084741/http://www.soapoperadigest.com/natalie-hall-bio|archivedate=April 7, 2014|df=}}</ref> (born January 25, 1990)<ref name=BiographySopa /> is a Canadian actress and singer. She has appeared in various Broadway, film and TV productions. Her first TV appearance was when she portrayed the role of [[Colby Chandler (All My Children)|Colby Chandler]] on the soap opera ''[[All My Children]]'' from 2009 to 2011. Hall appeared opposite [[Miles Teller]], [[Josh Brolin]] and [[Jeff Bridges]] in the 2017 film ''[[Only the Brave (2017 film)|Only the Brave]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nNatalie grew up in Vancouver, British Columbia prior to moving to New York to pursue roles on Broadway. Hall's mother was a ballerina. Hall grew up with two brothers, of which she has said \"I grew up loving the arts but I also was such a tomboy, I loved sports and was very competitive.\" She grew up playing soccer on an all-boys soccer team.<ref name=BiographySopa />\n\nShe performed as Val in the Broadway  production of ''[[A Chorus Line]]''.<ref name=BiographySopa /> Hall spoke about her first role, saying \"It was an amazing experience. I had to grow up so fast working with such talent on a big stage\". Her portrayal of Val earned her a [[Ovation (award)|Ovation award]]. Hall moved to [[New York City]] to pursue her dreams of [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] and TV stardom, and relocated to Los Angeles in 2010.<ref name=BiographySopa />\n\n==Career==\n===Acting===\n[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] announced that Hall had been cast in the role of [[Colby Chandler (All My Children)|Colby Chandler]] in the soap ''[[All My Children]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soaps.sheknows.com/allmychildren/news/id/5587/|title=Breaking News! All My Children Casts Natalie Hall as Colby!|date=October 3, 2009|work=Soaps She Knows|publisher=Atomic Online|accessdate=May 6, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402104619/http://soaps.sheknows.com/allmychildren/news/id/5587/|archive-date=April 2, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> Hall made her debut on November 25, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boards.soapcentral.com/amc/news/2009/1005-moncrief.php|title=Brianne Moncrief out, Colby Chandler recast|date=September 30, 2009|first=Dan J.|last=Kroll|work=[[SoapCentral]]|accessdate=May 6, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222213031/http://www.boards.soapcentral.com/amc/news/2009/1005-moncrief.php|archivedate=February 22, 2014|df=}}</ref> Hall filmed her first scenes in mid October just before the show relocated to [[Los Angeles]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://michaelfairmansoaps.com/news/natalie-hall-in-as-new-colby-on-amc/2009/10/02/|title=Natalie Hall IN as new Colby on \"AMC\"!|date=October 2, 2009|first=Michael|last=Fairman|work=On-Air On-Soaps|accessdate=May 6, 2013}}</ref> Hall made her last appearance in the final network broadcast of ''All My Children'' on September 23, 2011.\n\nOn June 29, 2011, it was announced that Hall would be replacing Natalie Floyd as Hanna's soon-to-be stepsister, Kate Randall, in the [[ABC Family]] series ''[[Pretty Little Liars]]'', playing the role until 2012.<ref>{{cite web |last=Bonner |first=Mehera |url=http://www.wetpaint.com/pretty-little-liars/articles/natalie-hall-replaces-natalie-floyd-as-hannas-wicked-stepsister-kate-on-pretty-little-liars |title=Natalie Hall Replaces Natalie Floyd as Hanna's Wicked Stepsister, Kate, on Pretty Little Liars |publisher=[[Wetpaint]] |date=June 29, 2011 |accessdate=July 7, 2011}}</ref> She played Ellie King n\u00e9e Davis, in ''[[Love's Christmas Journey]]'', a four-part mini-series in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/all-my-children-actress-star-220942 |title='All My Children' Actress to Star in Hallmark Mini 'Love's Christmas Journey' (Exclusive) |publisher=Hollywoodreporter.com |date=October 8, 2011 |accessdate=August 21, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, she was cast as Taylor in [[The CW]] series ''[[Star-Crossed (TV series)|Star-Crossed]]''.<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.caravanstyliststudio.com/natalie-hall-staring-in-star-crossed-a-new-show-on-the-cw-visits-caravan-stylist-studio-at-the-carlton-hotel/4133/ |title=Natalie Hall starring in \"Star Crossed\" a new show on the CW visits Caravan Stylist Studio at The Carlton Hotel |publisher=Caravan Stylist Studio |date=May 23, 2013 |accessdate=August 21, 2013}}</ref> Hall described her character as the \"Queen Bee with a big heart\" and a risk-taker in love.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Vogt|first1=Tiffany|title=STAR-CROSSED Scoop: Natalie Hall Talks Playing the Queen Bee of Marshall High|url=http://www.thetvaddict.com/2014/02/12/star-crossed-scoop-natalie-hall-talks-playing-the-queen-bee-of-marshall-high/|publisher=The TV Addict|accessdate=October 31, 2014}}</ref> Hall played Britney in the series revival of [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]] comedy-drama ''[[Drop Dead Diva]]'' originally for two episodes however came back for another episode.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Nededog|first1=Jethro|title=\u2018Pretty Little Liars\u2019 Natalie Hall in, Josh Stamberg out at \u2018Drop Dead Diva\u2019|url=https://www.thewrap.com/tv/article/pretty-little-liars-natalie-hall-josh-stamberg-out-drop-dead-diva-95586/|publisher=The Wrap|accessdate=October 31, 2014}}</ref> Hall joined the cast of [[HBO]]'s ''[[True Blood]]'' for its [[True Blood (season 7)|final season]], appearing as resident villain [[Sarah Newlin]]'s ([[Anna Camp]]) newly turned vampire sister, Amber Mills, for three episodes.<ref name=FaveMag>{{cite web|last1=Tsoumbakos|first1=Rachel|title=True Blood\u2019s Natalie Hall Graces Cover of Fave Magazine: The Canadian Fashion Magazine Available from October 2014|url=http://truebloodnet.com/true-bloods-natalie-hall-graces-cover-of-fave-magazine/|accessdate=October 31, 2014}}</ref> She appeared on the cover of the Canadian [[fashion magazine]] ''Fave''.<ref name=FaveMag />\n\nHall guested starred in [[USA Network]] medical [[comedy-drama]] ''[[Royal Pains]]'' as Hope, a [[burlesque]] dancer who turns to Jeremiah for help when she begins experiencing pain during her act.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deadline.com/2014/06/royal-pains-season-six-cast-usa-network/|title=5 Set For Season 6 Of USA\u2019s \u2018Royal Pains\u2019|publisher=Deadline.com|date=June 4, 2014|accessdate=June 5, 2014}}</ref> Hall is also a member of the Prestigious \"Actors Studio\" in New York. Hall was most recently cast in the upcoming untitled Marc Cherry ABC pilot. Natalie Hall was seen in UnREAL season four on Lifetime. Also, in the CW series ''[[Charmed]]'' playing Lucy.\n\n===Music===\nHall performs in various musicals in New York. Hall was trained at the London Academy of Ballet and graduated with honors of distinction in dance when she was sixteen. In the film ''[[Rising Stars (film)|Rising Stars]]'', Hall performed \"Better with You\", the music video for the song featuring Hall was later released.<ref name=RisingStars>{{cite web|title=Rising Stars (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/rising-stars-original-motion/id404326073|publisher=[[iTunes]]|accessdate=April 7, 2014}}</ref> She was also featured in the song \"Free To Fall\" which also appeared in the film and the official soundtrack.<ref name=RisingStars/> Hall performed \"[[Hallelujah I Love Her So]]\" by [[Ray Charles]] at the \"[[It Gets Better Project]]'s \"A Better Holiday\" concert benefiting The Ali Forney Center on December 16, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|last=Alexander|first=Clint|title=Natalie Hall - \"Hallelujah I Love Her So\"|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M3b0snYA3Qg|accessdate=April 7, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n<!-- Please note: \"rowspan\" breaks table sortability. -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|2004\n|''Have You Heard? Secret Central''\n|Tes Taylor\n|\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Rising Stars (film)|Rising Stars]]''\n|Brenna\n|\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[+1 (film)|+1]]''\n|Melanie\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''Lucky N#mbr''\n|Nikki Page\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[Simple Little Lives]]''\n|Kaylee\n|\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''{{sortname|The|Curse of Sleeping Beauty}}''\n| Linda Coleman\n| \n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Summer of 8]]''\n|Jen\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[The Boy Downstairs]]''\n|Ivy\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Only the Brave (2017 film)|''Only the Brave'']]''\n|Natalie Johnson\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n<!-- Please note: \"rowspan\" breaks table sortability. -->\n{| cla